<div class="glyphicon-adjust">
    <h1> History</h1>
</div>

<br />


<div>
    <div>
        <img src="~/ImageLogo/DevBhumi2.jpg" style="width:400px; height:300px" align="left" />
    </div>

    <div class="aboutus-content">
        <p>
            Uttarakhand is known as “Dev Bhumi”- The land of Gods, Yoga capital of the world,
            Home of the holy rivers, The Himalayan abode and we are fortunate enough to call it our Hometown.
            It is here where the journey, that has touched thousands of lives, began!
            This journey commenced in 1995 when Taradatt Phuloria, a visionary and our President,
            decided to contribute small donations to a school in Uttarakhand. Due to the inability of parents
            to pay the fees of their children and insufficient fund, the school management thought to shut down
            the school in the year 2014. At the same time, the Principal along with some of the parents & other
            management people requested Mr. Phuloria to save the school and allow the students to continue their
            education at bare minimum fees. This is what gave birth to the idea of running the school under
            the umbrella of Tulsi Foundation.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<br />
<br />

<div>
