    <div class="aboutus-content">
        <p>
            “It is challenging to initiate noble work, but the individual who envisions a tree in only a
            seed can take on this journey.”
            Mr. Chandrashekhar Phuloria was born and educated in a small village of Uttarakhand until 12th
            standard and later moved to Mumbai for further studies. He has an in-depth exposure to people in
            all walks of life and has vast experience in social work. He is held to a high-esteem by his family,
            friends and colleagues for his graciousness and compassion.
            Though he left his village, the culture and education system of rural India had made a lasting
            impression on him. His experiences motivated him to create Tulsi Foundation in 2011, as a way to
            contribute back to society. He is a firm believer in “Soch Badlo, Desh Badlega” which then became the
            motto of Tulsi Foundation.
        </p>
